# Architecture & Stack

## Stack (decided)
- **Go 1.26**, **Gin** (HTTP), **GORM** + Postgres driver (DB/ORM), **PostgreSQL 16**.
- Config via `envconfig`; structured logging via stdlib `slog` (JSON).
- Migrations: GORM `AutoMigrate` + raw SQL for partial unique indexes / check constraints.
- Docker + Docker Compose (app + Postgres); `Makefile` for common tasks.

## Layout (layered / hexagonal-lite)
```
cmd/marketd/            # entrypoint: server + workers + graceful shutdown
internal/
  config/               # env config
  domain/               # pure entities + business rules (NO I/O, unit-tested)
  service/              # use-cases; owns DB transaction boundaries
  ports/                # interfaces (repositories, oracle)
  adapters/
    http/               # Gin handlers, DTOs, middleware (idempotency)
    postgres/           # GORM repository implementations
    oracle/             # oracle client + mock
  worker/               # auction settlement ticker
migrations/  docs/
```

## Rules
- Keep `domain/` pure and dependency-free; put orchestration + transactions in `service/`.
- Enforce concurrency/uniqueness invariants at the **DB level** (constraints + `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE`),
  never solely in Go memory.
- Handlers stay thin: validate/parse → call service → map result to HTTP.
- Money as integer minor units, never floats.
